reviews.review_text: Keeps Gettin' Better Great work yet again.  This sounds fantastic and the show is also top notch.  First set hops and bops like most fall/winter 79 shows, with the band in high-energy mode (the 15+ minute Dancin is very, very nice).  The second set pre-drums run is a true work of art.  The Scarlet/Fire is not overly long, but features some great work by Jerry, especially in the transition jam.  Passenger if off the charts.  Terrapin is OK (Jerry's voice has a little trouble here and there), but the real gem is the Playin'.  The outro-jam is amazing with a sweet, sweet transition to drums.  Very spacey, but still tight.  Maybe not a 5 star, but I cant choose 4.5.  Certainly worth a listen.

I ran into Charlie Fog.. Good solid set list, Another classic from the Stanley.
